f-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><font color="#000000"><span style="caret-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">Engage Your Core</span></font></h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1701128048879" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1701128048879" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>One of the best <a href="https://www.healthdigest.com/892126/the-real-health-benefits-of-using-sliders/" class="" target="_blank">benefits</a> of sliders is that they engage your core in almost every movement. Many slider exercises involve balance, which ensures that your core is working during the exercise.&nbsp;</p><p>They add instability, which makes your core work harder to keep you balanced.&nbsp;</p><p>Sliders also challenge all three planes of motion, especially when you have to twist and turn.</p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1701128048826" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1701128048826"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><font color="#000000"><span style="caret-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">Balance and Agility Training</span></font></h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1701128048850" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1701128048850" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Typically, your workout programs will involve a lot of high-impact exercises like barbell and dumbbell movements. These can be valuable for your overall health but can neglect other vital parts such as <a href="https://www.verywellfit.com/full-body-workout-with-exercise-sliding-discs-4129112" class="" target="_blank">balance</a>, addressing muscular imbalances, and unilateral training.</p><p>Sliders work well for this type of training because you’re often working unilaterally, which can help address any imbalances while improving overall agility and balance.</p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1701128049011" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1701128049011"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><span style="caret-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">Portability</span></h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1701128048835" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1701128048835" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>A downside to many workout tools and equipment is that they aren’t highly portable. Meaning, you can’t bring them with you if you have to travel. But, sliders don’t have that issue. A vast majority of sliders weigh around a pound and take up very little space.</p><p>So, you can easily carry them with you in your bag or luggage and not miss your workout plan.</p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1701128048979" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1701128048979"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><font color="#000000"><span style="caret-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">Bodyweight Workouts</span></font></h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1701128048834" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1701128048834" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Some of the most common bodyweight workouts are planks, push-ups and mountain climbers. However, an issue with bodyweight exercises can be that you cannot consistently progress in them as well as weighted exercises. So, by adding a new layer of challenge, like sliders, you can increase the difficulty of your workout and make further progress.&nbsp;</p></div></div><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1701128048830" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1701128048830" data-resolution="3000x3000"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs gf-elm-center-lg" data-exc=""><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/413eef9e-5ec9-42ef-8e3b-64e7505a11c5/-/format/auto/-/preview/3000x3000/-/quality/lighter/slider-exercises.jpeg" alt="sliders for working out " class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" width="2121" height="1414" data-width="100%" data-height="auto" title="" natural-width="2121" natural-height="1414"></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1701128049002" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1701128049002"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">What to Look For in Exercise Sliders?</h2></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1701128049022" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1701128049022"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><span style="caret-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">Versatility</span></h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1701128049014" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1701128049014" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Versatility is an important factor when it comes to picking out the right slider. There are many environments you can use sliders in for example carpets, rugs, hardwood, pavement, tiled floors, turf, track, gym floors, gravel, mats, and polished cement.&nbsp;</p><p>Typically, if it's a dual-sided slider, it will be more versatile. However, the importance of versatility mainly depends on the user. If you know you’re gonna work out on one specific floor, then you can pick out one that meets those conditions.</p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1701128048831" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1701128048831"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><span style="caret-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">Material</span></h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1701128048828" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1701128048828" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>A slider can be made of many different materials. The two most common ones are plastic and foam. These tend to glide the best and have the least amount of friction. There are sliders which come with specialized plastic or foam too, in order to enhance durability.</p></div></div><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1701128049006" class="gf_row gf_row-gap-0" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1701128049006" data-row-gap="0px" data-extraclass="" style=""><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-12 gf_col-md-12 gf_col-sm-12 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1686320640542" data-id="1686320640542"><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1701128049023" class="gf_row gf_row-gap-0" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1701128049023" data-layout-lg="6+6" data-extraclass="" data-layout-md="6+6" data-layout-sm="6+6" data-layout-xs="8+4" data-row-gap="0px"><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-6 gf_col-md-6 gf_col-sm-6 gf_col-xs-8" id="c-1686566620521" data-id="1686566620521"><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1701128049024" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1701128049024"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><b>Tips From the Champ</b></h2></div></div></div><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-6 gf_col-md-6 gf_col-sm-6 gf_col-xs-4" id="c-1686566621695" data-id="1686566621695"><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1701128048829" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1701128048829" data-resolution="3000x3000"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-right-lg gf-elm-right-md gf-elm-right-sm gf-elm-right-xs" data-exc=""><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/d583efb1-a2f6-4d53-8a26-d6ddafaa60fd/7350738.png" alt="" class="gf_