ta-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1701128049031" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Durability is highly dependent on the material. If the material is high-quality, then the sliders will be more durable. Also, following the instructions is key for durability, as well. You have to make sure you’re using the sliders on the correct surfaces.&nbsp;</p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1701128049033" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1701128049033"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><span style="caret-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">Price/Quality</span></h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1701128049034" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1701128049034" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Generally, sliders are considered one of the more inexpensive workout tools. Many also come with a warranty to make it easier to invest in the product. Also, to get the most out of your money, a dual-sided slider can be more valuable as you can work out in more areas.&nbsp;</p></div></div><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1701128049036" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1701128049036" data-resolution="3000x3000"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs gf-elm-center-lg" data-exc=""><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/47fc2fd8-a187-453c-8c63-c1bb034c2a88/-/format/auto/-/preview/3000x3000/-/quality/lighter/sliders-for-working-out.jpeg" alt="exercise gliders for feet" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" width="2880" height="1923" data-width="100%" data-height="auto" title="" natural-width="2880" natural-height="1923"></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1701128049035" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1701128049035"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">How to Use Exercise Sliders Correctly?</h2></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1701128049037" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1701128049037"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><ul><li><span style="letter-spacing: 0px;">Test the sliders before performing your exercise. Some people find that the sliders can have too much friction or the opposite where they are too slippery. So, before actually exercising, test out the sliders’ gliding ability. This way you can avoid possible injury&nbsp;</span></li><li><span style="letter-spacing: 0px;">Start slow. If you’re not used to working out with sliders or haven’t done agility/balance training before, then it’s best that you start with some entry-level exercises. These can be <a href="https://www.womenshealthmag.com/fitness/g27090615/exercise-sliders/" class="" target="_blank">exercises</a> like the body saw, mountain climbers, and knee tucks</span></li><li><span style="letter-spacing: 0px;">Try using a timer rather than a rep count. Most people are used to the traditional set and rep range, like 3 sets of 8-12 repetitions. However, with sliders, timing your exercise can provide a better burn and results. So, if you’re new to slider workouts, you can try a set of 15 seconds and then progress your way up to 30 seconds and eventually even a full minute of work.&nbsp;</span></li></ul></div></div><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1701128049038" class="gf_row gf_row-gap-0" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1701128049038" data-row-gap="0px" data-extraclass="" data-layout-lg="12" data-layout-md="12" data-layout-sm="12" data-layout-xs="12" style="display: block;"><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-12 gf_col-md-12 gf_col-sm-12 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1658828961229" data-id="1658828961229"><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1701128049040" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1701128049040"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">FAQs</h2></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1701128049041" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1701128049041"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Are exercise sliders worth it?</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1701128049039" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1701128049039"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">Exercise sliders have a lot of benefits, which make them worth it. You will improve your balance and agility, as well as increase overall core stre